# Wallet Client Comparison

## Overview
Both [wallet_client.py](file:///c:/Users/rovie%20segubre/agent/wallet_client.py) and [smart_wallet.py](file:///c:/Users/rovie%20segubre/agent/smart_wallet.py) implement automatic token rotation, but they serve different purposes in your architecture.

---

## Side-by-Side Comparison

| Feature | [wallet_client.py](file:///c:/Users/rovie%20segubre/agent/wallet_client.py) | [smart_wallet.py](file:///c:/Users/rovie%20segubre/agent/smart_wallet.py) |
|---------|-------------------|------------------|
| **Purpose** | **API Client Library** | **End-User Chat Interface** |
| **Storage Format** | JSON (`wallet.json`) | Plain Text (`current_token.txt`) |
| **Storage Path** | [.agent/data/wallet.json](file:///c:/Users/rovie%20segubre/agent/.agent/data/wallet.json) | [.agent/wallet/current_token.txt](file:///c:/Users/rovie%20segubre/agent/.agent/wallet/current_token.txt) |
| **Interface** | Class-based ([SovereignWallet](file:///c:/Users/rovie%20segubre/agent/wallet_client.py#11-86)) | Function-based |
| **Default Behavior** | Single request (CLI args) | Interactive loop |
| **Use Case** | Import into other scripts | Direct human interaction |
| **Output Style** | Clean, structured | Conversational with emoji |

---

## Code Architecture

### [wallet_client.py](file:///c:/Users/rovie%20segubre/agent/wallet_client.py) - Library Approach
```python
from wallet_client import SovereignWallet

wallet = SovereignWallet("my_bot_wallet.json")
response = wallet.request_compute("sovereign-r1", "Hello")
print(response)
```

**Best for:**
- Building other AI agents
- Programmatic access
- Multiple wallet files
- Import as a module

---

### [smart_wallet.py](file:///c:/Users/rovie%20segubre/agent/smart_wallet.py) - Application Approach
```bash
python smart_wallet.py
> Hello
> What is 2+2?
> exit
```

**Best for:**
- Direct human testing
- Quick conversations
- Single persistent wallet
- Standalone executable

